# Frontend Engineering Rules

You are a **senior React/TypeScript frontend engineer**. Read
`.claude/agents/frontend-engineer/AGENT.md` and its `MEMORY.md` before
starting any frontend task.

## Component Patterns

- Functional components only (no class components)
- Components in PascalCase files: `NeedView.tsx`, `DetailPanel.tsx`
- Hooks prefixed with `use`: `useModel.ts`, `useAIEnabled.ts`

## Styling

- Tailwind CSS utility classes as primary styling method
- CSS variables for theme values (`text-muted-foreground`, `bg-background`)
- shadcn/ui copy-paste pattern (not npm installed) for base components
- Lucide React for icons — do not add other icon libraries
- Inline styles only as last resort (dynamic pixel values from data)

## State & Data

- `useModel()` for model ID propagation — never hardcode
- All API calls via `@/lib/api.ts` — never raw `fetch` in components
- Handle **loading**, **error**, and **empty** states for every data fetch
- Wrap model-dependent pages with `<ModelRequired>` — do not implement custom guards

## Standard View Pattern

```typescript
export function MyView() {
  const { modelId } = useModel()
  const [data, setData] = useState<T | null>(null)
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true)
  const [error, setError] = useState<string | null>(null)

  useEffect(() => {
    if (!modelId) return
    api.getData(modelId)
      .then(setData)
      .catch(e => setError(e.message))
      .finally(() => setLoading(false))
  }, [modelId])

  if (loading) return <LoadingState />
  if (error) return <ErrorState message={error} />
  if (!data) return <EmptyState />

  return <div>{/* render data */}</div>
}
```

## UX Rules

- Every warning/error icon MUST have accompanying text — no icon-only indicators
- Disabled elements show `opacity-50`, never `opacity-0`
- Floating panels MUST close on click-outside
- Numbers shown with context: "14 services", not "14"

## Frontend Displays, Backend Computes

The frontend MUST NOT compute derived data (ratios, scores, risk levels).
All signals and computed values come from the backend API. The frontend
renders what the API provides.

## Validation

ALWAYS run before declaring done:

```bash
cd frontend && npm run build   # tsc -b && vite build (matches CI/Dockerfile)
```

Must pass with zero errors.
